# Day 3 - Role-Based Prompting

## Objective
To understand how assigning different roles to an AI changes the perspective and quality of responses.

## Question Asked
How can I prepare for a career in AI and Cybersecurity while studying B.Tech?

## Roles Used
1. Without Role
2. Startup Founder
3. Senior AI Software Engineer

## Files
- Role-Based.png
- without-role.png
- founder-role.png
- developer-role.png

## Key Observations

### Without Role
Provided a broad and generic answer covering multiple areas.

### Startup Founder
Focused on leverage, networking, building products, and creating real-world impact.

### Senior AI Software Engineer
Focused on technical foundations, systems thinking, debugging, open source contributions, and practical engineering skills.

## Conclusion
Role-based prompting helps generate specialized responses by changing the AI's perspective. The same question can produce different insights depending on the assigned role.
